<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <head>No. 446.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morris</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Cable telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-06-04"><hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 4,
                                1870</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Constantinople:</hi></p>
                        <p>It is reported by telegraph that extensive murders of Jews have taken
                            place in Roumania. Ascertain facts, and, if true, unofficially urge on
                            Turkish government to put a stop to bloodshed. Answer by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>